unfold

Display enclosing brace context of grep search results for c-like languages
e.g. to display enclosing classes, traits.. for search results
eases searching through deeply nested source from the commandline

requires filenames and line numbers emitted by grep; works from stdin->stdout

useage:
grep -rn something_interesting . --include <desired source> |unfold

output of grep:-
somefile.cpp:75:             void foo();
another.rs:130:        fn foo();

output of unfold:-
somefile.cpp:60-     namespace Yada
somefile.cpp:61-     {
somefile.cpp:68-         class Foo {
somefile.cpp:75:             void foo();
another.rs:38-     mod apple {
another.rs:68-         trait Banana {
another.rs:130:            fn foo();

